Task 1 – Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic

Tool Used -

The tool used to create this infographic is Canva (canva.com). I chose to use Canva as it is free 
and can be accessed through a browser. It also provides much better results than other tools such as PowerPoint. 
Additionally, it does not need to be downloaded onto the computer, making it a convenient option for use. 

What the Infographic Includes - 
The infographic is designed to be a one-page visual and is divided into three major parts:

1. Understanding Digital Literacy: In this section of the infographic, I chose to explain digital literacy not through 
the general definition provided in a textbook but through the following five major aspects: "searching for information," 
"communicating," "creating digital content," "online safety," and "using technology to solve problems." Each of these aspects
is described in an easy-to-understand manner. 

2. Helpful Tools for Students - In this section of the infographic, I chose to highlight the various platforms available to 
students and categorized these platforms based on their uses for students. For instance, platforms such as GitHub, LinkedIn,
and Kaggle are used for creating professional profiles for students. Similarly, platforms such as HackerRank and CodeChef 
are used for coding practice by students during their college days. Google Drive and Google Forms are also used for collaboration
among students, while NPTEL and Coursera are used for learning purposes. 

3. Safe Internet Practices - In this section of the infographic, I chose to highlight the various aspects of internet safety 
and how these aspects need to be followed by students for their own safety while using the internet for various purposes. 
The aspects of internet safety include the use of passwords and two-factor authentication for added safety and how to identify 
phishing and other UPI scams."






